  &lt;p id="DMcUqE"&gt;For someone who wants to spend the absolute &lt;em&gt;least&lt;/em&gt; on a phone and not have to think about buying another one for a good long while, I’ll always recommend Google’s A-series Pixel phone. That’s doubly true now with &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/24162073/google-pixel-8a-review-specs-price-camera"&gt;the Pixel 8A&lt;/a&gt; on a $100 discount for &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/24288220/black-friday-best-deals-guide-cyber-monday-tech-gadgets-2024"&gt;Black Friday-ish Cyber Shopping Holiday&lt;/a&gt; or whatever it is we’re currently experiencing. The 8A is a solid value at its full $499 price, and cut down to $399 it’s a ridiculously good deal.&lt;/p&gt;
